CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 18, 1956, pg. 2 reads: ""Family of Seventeen Arrives From South - Newcomers To Pittsburgh - William Wofford, 42, his wife, Irene who is shown holding the youngest member of the family, have brought their family of fifteen children to Pittsburgh after nearly starving as tenant-farmer in Bell City, Mo. Wofford was recently laid off a job and now is tramping throughout the city to find another. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Wofford family, including William Wofford wearing suspenders, wife Irene holding baby Donald Roy, and their fifteen children, gathered in interior with tree patterned wallpaper, 1631 Our Alley
